    followUp:
      'Why is it safe to never decrement maxFreq when shrinking the window? Because the answer is monotone in maxFreq: if a window of length L worked, increasing maxFreq can only make it work again with the same or larger L. A stale maxFreq can never produce a longer valid window than the true one — the window simply will not expand past the previous best until a fresh max-frequency value catches up.',
    similar: ['longest-substring-without-repeating-characters', 'max-consecutive-ones-iii', 'permutation-in-string', 'minimum-window-substring', 'find-all-anagrams-in-a-string'],
